import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['miles'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['miles'] = pd.to_numeric(data['miles'], errors='coerce')
    data['gas'] = pd.to_numeric(data['gas'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'])
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Consumption')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between miles driven and gas consumption?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(data['year'].dt.year)['gas'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['year'], data['gas'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['gas'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend(['Average gas consumption'])
    plt.title('What is the average gas consumption per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['year'], bins=20, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['year'].min(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Min year: {data['year'].min().strftime('%Y')}")
    ax.axvline(data['year'].max(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Max year: {data['year'].max().strftime('%Y')}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of years in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['side', pd.Grouper(key='year', freq='Y')])['miles'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for key, grp in data.groupby(['side']):
        ax = grp.plot(ax=ax, kind='line', x='year', y='miles', label=key)
    plt.title('What is the average miles driven per side?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
